---
import BaseLayout from '@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="How I verify"
  description="How I decide what to list, what to reject, and how often I re-check. Built and verified by Sarthak — no clones, no AI slop, no broken demos."
>
  <section class="container-page pt-14 pb-10 md:pt-20">
    <p class="kicker">How I verify</p>
    <h1 class="mt-3 text-4xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-fg sm:text-5xl text-balance">
      Built. Tested. Re-verified.
    </h1>
    <p class="mt-5 max-w-2xl text-[15px] text-muted leading-relaxed text-pretty">
      I ship every Base here myself. The point of this site is trust — so I'd rather
      list fewer things, slower, than dump AI-generated repos online and hope. Here's
      what makes the cut, what doesn't, and how often I re-check.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="container-page py-12">
    <div class="grid gap-6 md:grid-cols-2">
      <div class="panel p-7">
        <p class="kicker">We accept</p>
        <ul class="mt-5 space-y-2.5 text-[15px] text-muted">
          {[
            'Original implementations',
            'SaaS-inspired workflows (alternatives, not clones)',
            'Source-code products',
            'Local-first tools',
            'Mac apps, websites, internal tools, mobile prototypes',
            'Privacy-friendly alternatives',
            'Remixable small apps with a clear niche',
          ].map((s) => (
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="mt-2 inline-block h-1.5 w-1.5 rounded-full" style="background: var(--color-verified);"></span>
              <span>{s}</span>
            </li>
          ))}
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="panel p-7">
        <p class="kicker" style="color: var(--color-warn);">We reject</p>
        <ul class="mt-5 space-y-2.5 text-[15px] text-muted">
          {[
            'Copied source code, UI, branding, or assets',
            'Generic todo / CRM / chatbot listings with no niche angle',
            'Broken demos',
            'Listings making misleading comparison claims',
            'Hidden telemetry, adware, malware',
            'Unsupported "AI slop"',
            'Products that violate third-party service terms',
          ].map((s) => (
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="mt-2 inline-block h-px w-2.5" style="background: var(--color-warn);"></span>
              <span>{s}</span>
            </li>
          ))}
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="container-page py-12">
    <header class="max-w-2xl">
      <p class="kicker">My process</p>
      <h2 class="mt-3 text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-fg sm:text-4xl text-balance">
        Five gates before a Base goes live.
      </h2>
    </header>

    <ol class="mt-8 grid gap-4 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-5">
      {[
        { n: '01', t: 'Build',       d: 'I ship the working version end-to-end. No "AI drafted, untested" hand-offs.' },
        { n: '02', t: 'Live for me', d: 'It runs in my own setup for at least a couple of weeks. Bugs surface; I fix them.' },
        { n: '03', t: 'Strip to scope', d: 'I cut anything that wasn\'t solid. The listing\'s does / does-not panels reflect what survived.' },
        { n: '04', t: 'Publish',     d: 'Badges issued (Live Preview, Source Build, Remix Ready). "Last verified" date stamped.' },
        { n: '05', t: 'Re-verify',   d: 'I re-check periodically and after upstream changes. Stale Bases get hidden until re-verified.' },
      ].map((step) => (
        <li class="panel p-5">
          <div class="font-mono text-xs tracking-[0.16em] text-accent">{step.n}</div>
          <h3 class="mt-2 text-base font-semibold text-fg">{step.t}</h3>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-muted leading-relaxed text-pretty">{step.d}</p>
        </li>
      ))}
    </ol>
  </section>

  <section class="container-page py-12">
    <div class="panel-2 grid gap-8 p-7 md:grid-cols-[1fr,1.4fr] md:p-10">
      <div>
        <p class="kicker">Anti-clone</p>
        <h2 class="mt-3 text-2xl font-semibold text-fg sm:text-3xl text-balance">
          We don't sell clones. We sell ownable alternatives.
        </h2>
      </div>
      <div class="space-y-4 text-[15px] text-muted leading-relaxed text-pretty">
        <p>Existing SaaS products are demand signals — not products to copy.</p>
        <ul class="space-y-3">
          <li><span class="font-mono text-xs text-[var(--color-danger)]">REJECTED</span> &nbsp; "Calendly clone"</li>
          <li><span class="font-mono text-xs text-verified">ACCEPTED</span> &nbsp; "Solo clinic booking Base with intake forms, deposits, private notes, and CSV export"</li>
          <li class="border-t border-line pt-3"><span class="font-mono text-xs text-[var(--color-danger)]">REJECTED</span> &nbsp; "Notion clone"</li>
          <li><span class="font-mono text-xs text-verified">ACCEPTED</span> &nbsp; "Private team wiki Base with markdown pages, search, and role-based access"</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="container-page py-12 pb-24">
    <div class="grid gap-6 md:grid-cols-3">
      {[
        { t: 'Honesty', d: 'Every listing shows free tools, paid SaaS alternatives, and a "should you just prompt this yourself?" section.' },
        { t: 'Limitations',  d: 'Mandatory. If the limitations field is empty, the Base doesn’t list.' },
        { t: 'Last verified', d: 'A timestamp every buyer can see. Stale verifications get hidden until re-checked.' },
      ].map((p) => (
        <div class="panel p-6">
          <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-fg">{p.t}</h3>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-muted leading-relaxed text-pretty">{p.d}</p>
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>

    <div class="mt-12 flex flex-wrap items-center gap-3 border-t border-line pt-8">
      <a href="/bases" class="btn btn-primary">Browse what's verified →</a>
      <a href="/collab" class="btn btn-ghost">Or send me what you built</a>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
